 what “becoming American” means for Iraqi refugees, even as they are perceived by other Americans as “security threats.”As debates about immigration and refugee status continue to play out in headlines and the courts, Iraqi Refugees in the United States provides important insight into the global refugee crisis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aImmigrantsxCultural assimilationzUnited States. 0aIraqiszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aIslamophobiazUnited States. 0aRefugeeszIraq. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aCultural Citizenship.  aCultural Citzenship.  aIraqi Resettlement.  aLatinx Immigrants.  aModel Minorities.  aRefugee Belonging.  aRefugee Crisis.  aRefugee Discrimination.  aRefugee Displacement.  aRefugee Migration.40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479849611.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479849611423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479849611/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles